<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,844,1952]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">
Male imago. Length: body, 
<quantity box="[498,652,844,870]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.65" metricValueMax="6.8" metricValueMin="6.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="6.65" valueMax="6.8" valueMin="6.5">6.5–6.8 mm</quantity>
; fore wing, 
<quantity box="[803,956,844,870]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.6" metricValueMax="6.7" metricValueMin="6.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="6.6" valueMax="6.7" valueMin="6.5">6.5–6.7 mm</quantity>
. General coloration (
<figureCitation box="[1220,1339,844,870]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="4.[151,272,1935,1959]" captionTargetBox="[252,1334,187,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-65@4.[252,1335,187,1911]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Askola. Figs 1–3, Askola emmerichi, sp. nov., male imago. 1, general aspect, lateral view; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view. Figs 4–6, Askola paprockii sp. nov., male imago. 4, body, dorsal view; 5, idem, ventral view; 6, head, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5319924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5319924/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Figs. 4–5</figureCitation>
) thorax yellowish white, wings and abdomen hyaline, with grayish marks. Head (
<figureCitation box="[1059,1136,882,908]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="4.[151,272,1935,1959]" captionTargetBox="[252,1334,187,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-65@4.[252,1335,187,1911]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Askola. Figs 1–3, Askola emmerichi, sp. nov., male imago. 1, general aspect, lateral view; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view. Figs 4–6, Askola paprockii sp. nov., male imago. 4, body, dorsal view; 5, idem, ventral view; 6, head, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5319924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5319924/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Dorsal portion of eyes grayish black, lower portion black; eyes widely meeting dorsally on meson of head; head yellowish white with two black stripes from eyes and ocelli to fore margin. Antennae whitish. Thorax yellowish white darker on meso and metanotum. Pronotum with blackish marks on lateral margins and two pairs of black sublateral spots. Mesonotum with a small black spot at base of wings and diffuse black marks from wing base to anterior margin. Metanotum with a pair of broad sublateral black marks. Pleurae with distinct black marks especially around coxae, sterna with central area washed with black. Legs yellowish white with slightly darker femora; trochanters II–III with black spots; subapical black band on tibia I; black medial mark on femora II–III. Wings (
<figureCitation box="[159,248,1192,1218]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–36" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[195,1385,727,1874]" captionTargetId="figure-302@10.[194,1393,727,1877]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 25–36. Askola. Figs 25–27, male fore wing: 25, Askola emmerichi sp.nov.; 26, Askola paprockii sp. nov.; 27, Askola cipoensis sp. nov. Figs 28–30, Askola emmerichi sp.nov.: 28, genitalia, ventral view; 29, genitalia, lateral view; 30, penes, detail. Figs 31–33, Askola paprockii sp. nov.: 31, genitalia, ventral view; 32, genitalia, lateral view; 33, penes, detail. Figs 34–36, Askola cipoensis sp. nov.: 34, genitalia, ventral view; 35, genitalia, lateral view; 36, penes, detail." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5319934" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5319934/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). Membrane hyaline except base of C area yellowish and grayish spots mainly around cross veins as in 
<figureCitation box="[182,268,1230,1256]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–36" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[195,1385,727,1874]" captionTargetId="figure-302@10.[194,1393,727,1877]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 25–36. Askola. Figs 25–27, male fore wing: 25, Askola emmerichi sp.nov.; 26, Askola paprockii sp. nov.; 27, Askola cipoensis sp. nov. Figs 28–30, Askola emmerichi sp.nov.: 28, genitalia, ventral view; 29, genitalia, lateral view; 30, penes, detail. Figs 31–33, Askola paprockii sp. nov.: 31, genitalia, ventral view; 32, genitalia, lateral view; 33, penes, detail. Figs 34–36, Askola cipoensis sp. nov.: 34, genitalia, ventral view; 35, genitalia, lateral view; 36, penes, detail." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5319934" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5319934/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
; longitudinal veins yellowish gray lighter towards hind margin, cross veins blackish bordered with grayish; 4 costal cross veins from bulla to costal brace. Abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[994,1113,1269,1295]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="4.[151,272,1935,1959]" captionTargetBox="[252,1334,187,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-65@4.[252,1335,187,1911]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Askola. Figs 1–3, Askola emmerichi, sp. nov., male imago. 1, general aspect, lateral view; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view. Figs 4–6, Askola paprockii sp. nov., male imago. 4, body, dorsal view; 5, idem, ventral view; 6, head, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5319924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5319924/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Figs. 4–5</figureCitation>
) translucent white except segments IX–X yellowish heavily washed with black. Tergum I completely washed with black, terga II–VIII with a black band on lateral and hind margins, except medial line; terga VII–VIII with a pair of submedian blackish spots near fore margin. Abdominal sternum I with anteromedian black mark and a pair of blackish wide diagonal stripes, sterna II–VII with small anterolateral spot and thin and short oblique blackish stripe ending on spiracles, sterna VIII–IX with lateral margins blackish. Genitalia: styliger plate whitish uniformly washed with gray, forceps whitish except basal half washed with gray, penes yellowish washed with gray. [Caudal filaments broken of and lost].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
